CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 19, 1966, pg. 12A reads: "Victorious Spartans - From the broad smiles on the faces of members of the Schenley High School basketball team and their coach Willard Fisher, kneeling center, it is apparent everything had just gone fine in last week's City Championship game. The Spartan's won against Allegheny, 87-52, for their second league crown in a row.  Schenley is now seeking the state championship.  Holding victory trophy is starter, Marvin Snowden. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of cheering Schenley High School basketball players including Donal Mulberry, Marvin Snowden holding City Championship plaque and Coach Willard Fisher, gathered in locker room
